WEBVTT



00:00:09.152 --> 00:00:19.200
Hi, Calvary. as we continue on our walk with Jesus, we find him entering into the city of Jerusalem for the triumphal entry. And and we're going to be looking at this from Matthew.

00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:25.088
to Matthew's perspective in chapter 21. So I'd like to read these few verses with us this morning.

00:00:26.048 --> 00:00:31.104
As they approached Jerusalem and came to Beth-age on the Mount of Olives, Jesus,

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:33.792
Sent two disciples saying to them,

00:00:33.664 --> 00:00:36.160
Go to the village ahead of you,

00:00:36.256 --> 00:00:40.352
And at once you will find Donkey tied there with her colt by her.

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:43.360
Untie them and bring them to me.

00:00:43.456 --> 00:00:47.232
If anyone says anything to you, say, "The Lord needs them."

00:00:47.296 --> 00:00:49.696
And he will send them right away.

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:53.344
This took place to fulfill what was spoken to the prophet.

00:00:53.568 --> 00:00:55.392
Say to daughter Zion,

00:00:55.264 --> 00:00:57.888
See, your King comes to you, gentle,

00:00:57.696 --> 00:00:59.488
and riding on a donkey,

00:00:59.264 --> 00:01:00.416
and a coal.

00:01:00.352 --> 00:01:02.112
The foal of a donkey.

00:01:02.496 --> 00:01:05.824
The disciples went and did as Jesus had instructed them.

00:01:06.048 --> 00:01:10.688
They brought the donkey and the colt and placed their cloaks on them for Jesus to sit on.

00:01:11.040 --> 00:01:16.832
A very large crowd spread their cloaks on the road while others cut branches from the trees and spread them on the road.

00:01:17.024 --> 00:01:21.024
The crowds that went ahead of him and those that followed shouted.

00:01:20.736 --> 00:01:22.816
who's Zana to the son of David.

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:25.696
Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord.

00:01:25.408 --> 00:01:28.096
Hosanna in the highest of heaven.

00:01:28.128 --> 00:01:32.768
And when Jesus entered Jerusalem, the whole city was stirred and asked, "Who is this?"

00:01:32.736 --> 00:01:38.368
The crowds answered, "This is Jesus, the prophet from Nazareth in Galilee."

00:01:38.944 --> 00:01:46.464
If you can imagine, there were thousands of people who were pouring into the city of Jerusalem in preparation and celebration of Passover.

00:01:46.592 --> 00:01:54.240
Jerusalem was teeming with energy and life, and it was at this moment that Jesus,

00:01:54.176 --> 00:02:00.352
was to enter Jerusalem to make public his claim as Messiah, Savior, and Savior.

00:02:00.064 --> 00:02:01.280
and King.

00:02:01.248 --> 00:02:04.544
He came into fulfillment of prophecy,

00:02:04.576 --> 00:02:12.512
But prior to his entering Jerusalem, there had been many thousands who had witnessed Jesus's miracles and his teachings.

00:02:12.896 --> 00:02:16.032
And they had come to believe that he would be

00:02:15.808 --> 00:02:17.632
The future king

00:02:17.408 --> 00:02:18.848
of Jerusalem.

00:02:19.104 --> 00:02:20.320
Not as,

00:02:20.128 --> 00:02:23.456
What we might think him to be, but as an earthly king.

00:02:23.264 --> 00:02:26.432
Someone who would overthrow Rome.

00:02:26.528 --> 00:02:30.496
But that wasn't Jesus' intentions for entering Jerusalem.

00:02:30.496 --> 00:02:34.144
He came really to fulfill Zechariah 9:9. This is what

00:02:34.528 --> 00:02:37.984
what it says it says rejoiced greatly oh daughter of Zion

00:02:38.016 --> 00:02:42.080
Shout, daughter of Jerusalem, see your king comes to you.

00:02:42.048 --> 00:02:44.800
Righteous and having salvation

00:02:44.672 --> 00:02:49.760
Gentle and riding on a donkey on a colt, the foal of a donkey.

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:55.424
Jesus' intention was to ride into that city, not as a warring king, but as someone who would

00:02:55.616 --> 00:02:58.784
Come gentle and meek and in humility.

00:02:58.912 --> 00:03:01.152
He would come as a lowly servant.

00:03:01.088 --> 00:03:03.936
Someone that would enter the city.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:06.048
With love and mercy.

00:03:06.400 --> 00:03:08.672
He was there to bring salvation.

00:03:08.672 --> 00:03:11.104
He was there to lay down his life.

00:03:11.264 --> 00:03:12.288
Four,

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:15.008
Them and for all humanity.

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:21.440
Jesus had no intentions of entering that city to conquer a nation or to take

00:03:21.408 --> 00:03:24.416
The rulership of being king.

00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:27.392
But he came to conquer the hearts and minds of

00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:28.288
of men.

00:03:29.344 --> 00:03:33.824
He didn't come to provide temporal peace. No, he came to provide peace.

00:03:33.600 --> 00:03:35.488
Everlasting peace.

00:03:35.584 --> 00:03:37.120
Through his father.

00:03:36.928 --> 00:03:38.944
That we all might experience

00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:40.352
In our daily lives.

00:03:40.416 --> 00:03:46.208
The people had come with great hope that Jesus would liberate them from Roman occupation.

00:03:46.496 --> 00:03:56.544
And so they were celebrating his entrance in the city by taking their coats off their backs and cutting branches from the trees and throwing them on the road before him in submission to him as to

00:03:56.064 --> 00:03:57.216
That's king. That's

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:00.416
It was their way of saying, "We are ready."

00:04:00.288 --> 00:04:03.328
to receive you as Messiah.

00:04:03.456 --> 00:04:04.800
Of our people.

00:04:04.992 --> 00:04:12.576
And they began to shout to him, "Hosanna to the Son of David! Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord!"

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:14.592
In the highest of heaven.

00:04:14.752 --> 00:04:17.664
In essence, what they were saying was, save us.

00:04:17.472 --> 00:04:19.072
Deliver us.

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:23.872
We acknowledge you as the righteous Davidic Messiah and King.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:29.024
And we offer our praise to you as our lord and coming savior.

00:04:29.792 --> 00:04:30.912
However,

00:04:30.688 --> 00:04:32.480
In a few short days,

00:04:32.416 --> 00:04:36.000
Jesus wouldn't meet up to their expectations.

00:04:36.416 --> 00:04:37.440
They would...

00:04:37.184 --> 00:04:43.424
See him no longer as the Messiah, the one who would take over the rule of their city.

00:04:43.488 --> 00:04:46.816
And so he would become rejected by them.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:51.200
I think what this story means to me

00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:53.408
Is first and foremost

00:04:53.344 --> 00:04:55.104
That Jesus

00:04:54.976 --> 00:04:56.000
Keeps.

00:04:55.808 --> 00:04:57.312
His promises.

00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:02.144
That from the beginning of time was sent under the world that he had a plan.

00:05:02.304 --> 00:05:04.704
That he had a purpose for mankind.

00:05:04.672 --> 00:05:09.440
And that he would come to rescue us, rescue the world from our own sin.

00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:11.712
And that he would come willingly.

00:05:11.584 --> 00:05:13.120
Intentionally

00:05:12.992 --> 00:05:15.776
And in great love lay down his life.

00:05:15.744 --> 00:05:17.120
For our sin

00:05:17.184 --> 00:05:18.624
For my sin,

00:05:18.432 --> 00:05:21.952
So that we might enjoy the grace and forgiveness

00:05:21.952 --> 00:05:23.040
of God.

00:05:23.712 --> 00:05:25.344
But he also came,

00:05:25.312 --> 00:05:27.008
as Messiah.

00:05:27.136 --> 00:05:31.872
He came as our Messiah, our deliverer, our rescuer from the power.

00:05:31.776 --> 00:05:32.864
Of sin.

00:05:33.248 --> 00:05:34.880
And for that reason,

00:05:34.816 --> 00:05:38.144
Jesus is worthy to be called king.

00:05:38.176 --> 00:05:39.840
He is worthy.

00:05:39.840 --> 00:05:45.184
to be served. He is worthy that we submit our lives to him, to give our hearts to him.

00:05:45.152 --> 00:05:48.032
to recognize him as our Lord.

00:05:47.968 --> 00:05:49.216
and Savior.

00:05:49.856 --> 00:05:51.104
How about you?

00:05:51.808 --> 00:05:55.072
Have you considered Jesus as your king?

00:05:55.776 --> 00:05:57.824
Have you considered why he came?

00:05:58.816 --> 00:06:02.560
Have you allowed him to be the savior and king of your life?

00:06:02.464 --> 00:06:05.248
To be your deliverer, your rescuer,

00:06:05.536 --> 00:06:07.328
To be your salvation

00:06:08.064 --> 00:06:09.664
You know he came.

00:06:09.632 --> 00:06:10.976
In love.

00:06:11.104 --> 00:06:12.672
In mercy,

00:06:12.672 --> 00:06:14.080
And grace

00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:16.864
So that we might know him in relationship.

00:06:17.792 --> 00:06:20.736
He is worthy of our praise and adoration.

00:06:21.344 --> 00:06:23.616
He is worthy of our hosannas.

00:06:23.488 --> 00:06:24.928
Blessed is he,

00:06:24.992 --> 00:06:27.392
Who comes in the name of the Lord.

00:06:27.424 --> 00:06:28.224
Thank you
